	dprr:hasNoteText "The Lex Ovinia assigned the lection of the Senate to the Censors (Fest. 290 L). Passed before the first lection in 312, but probably only{159} recently, since the Consuls refused to accept it as valid. See Rotondi 233; Niccolini FTP 389." .
